## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Performance Requirements

**NFR-P-001: Response Time**
- API responses must complete within {{RESPONSE_TIME_MS}}ms for 95th percentile
- Page load time must not exceed {{PAGE_LOAD_TIME}}s
- Database queries must complete within {{DB_QUERY_TIME}}ms

**NFR-P-002: Throughput**
- System must handle {{REQUESTS_PER_SECOND}} requests per second
- Support {{CONCURRENT_USERS}} concurrent users

**NFR-P-003: Resource Utilization**
- CPU utilization should not exceed {{CPU_THRESHOLD}}% under normal load
- Memory usage should not exceed {{MEMORY_THRESHOLD}}GB

### 4.2 Security Requirements

**NFR-S-001: Authentication**
- All users must authenticate using {{AUTH_METHOD}}
- Support multi-factor authentication (MFA)
- Session timeout after {{SESSION_TIMEOUT}} minutes of inactivity

**NFR-S-002: Authorization**
- Implement role-based access control (RBAC)
- Enforce principle of least privilege
- Audit all access to sensitive data

**NFR-S-003: Data Protection**
- Encrypt data in transit using TLS 1.3
- Encrypt sensitive data at rest using {{ENCRYPTION_ALGORITHM}}
- Implement data masking for {{SENSITIVE_FIELDS}}

**NFR-S-004: Compliance**
- Comply with {{COMPLIANCE_STANDARD}} (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, SOC2)
- Support data retention policies
- Provide audit trail for all data modifications

### 4.3 Reliability Requirements

**NFR-R-001: Availability**
- System uptime must be {{UPTIME_PERCENTAGE}}% (e.g., 99.9%)
- Maximum planned downtime: {{PLANNED_DOWNTIME}} per month
- Maximum unplanned downtime: {{UNPLANNED_DOWNTIME}} per month

**NFR-R-002: Fault Tolerance**
- System must gracefully handle {{FAILURE_SCENARIOS}}
- Implement circuit breaker pattern for external service calls
- Support automatic failover for critical components

**NFR-R-003: Data Integrity**
- Zero data loss for committed transactions
- Support point-in-time recovery up to {{RECOVERY_POINT}}  
- Implement database ACID guarantees

### 4.4 Scalability Requirements

**NFR-SC-001: Horizontal Scaling**
- Support horizontal scaling to {{MAX_INSTANCES}} instances
- Stateless application design for load balancing
- Auto-scaling based on {{SCALING_METRICS}}

**NFR-SC-002: Data Scalability**
- Support {{DATA_VOLUME}} of data storage
- Handle growth rate of {{GROWTH_RATE}} per year

### 4.5 Usability Requirements

**NFR-U-001: User Interface**
- Interface must be intuitive for {{USER_EXPERTISE_LEVEL}} users
- Support {{ACCESSIBILITY_STANDARD}} (e.g., WCAG 2.1 Level AA)
- Responsive design for desktop, tablet, and mobile devices

**NFR-U-002: Learnability**
- New users should complete {{KEY_TASK}} within {{LEARNING_TIME}} minutes
- Provide in-app help and tooltips
- Support {{LANGUAGES}} languages

### 4.6 Maintainability Requirements

**NFR-M-001: Code Quality**
- Maintain code coverage above {{COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}%
- Follow {{CODING_STANDARD}} coding standards
- Document all public APIs

**NFR-M-002: Monitoring**
- Implement comprehensive logging with log levels
- Provide real-time monitoring dashboards
- Alert on {{ALERT_CONDITIONS}}

### 4.7 Compatibility Requirements

**NFR-C-001: Browser Support**
- Support latest 2 versions of Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- Graceful degradation for older browsers

**NFR-C-002: API Compatibility**
- Maintain backward compatibility for {{API_VERSION_SUPPORT}} versions
- Provide API versioning strategy

